I think this show is magical The set list, the way they play the songs, for example the Sampson intro is really interesting.  Keith it's in full genius mode, Donna is on point, Jerry is inspired and Bob and Phil are just right.  I am partial to the Keith era, and this show doesn't disappoint.  5 stars!
Don't miss this one Mellow show. Standout Crazy Fingers, in my opinion, among others. Good set list, good show!

Very solid comeback show I hesitate to give this 5 stars, but in the context of being the first show in over 8 months, and their first true "comeback" performance, this is a very fine show. Scarlet has a very nice, mellow jam that wanders but never strays. Same goes for the Help>Slip, which is probably the most exploratory to date. Crazy Fingers is not quite 6/14/76, but very well done. Let it Grow is also pretty nice, if a bit unfocused. 

The highlight of the entire show just might be the Dancin: this version is unique to those performed later on the tour, partly because Garcia employs a very gritty, dirty tone that just sounds amazing! The jam is also more aggressive and funkier than usual. I'll go out on a limb and declare this one of the best "Disco" Dancin's ever, in fact.
